'''Lucas Herrington''' (born 5 September 2007) is an Australian professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[central defender]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Colorado Rapids]] and the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]].

==Club career==

=== Brisbane Roar ===
Herrington is a product of the youth systems of [[Taringa Rovers SFC|Taringa Rovers]], [[Toowong FC]] and [[Brisbane City FC]], before joining the academy of [[Brisbane Roar FC|Brisbane Roar]] in 2019, where he completed his development.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://brisbaneroar.com.au/player/lucas-herrington/ |title=Lucas Herrington |website=Brisbane Roar FC}}</ref> In 2023, he featured for the club’s reserve side, [[Brisbane Roar FC Youth|Brisbane Roar Youth]].

On 9 September 2024, he signed a three-year scholarship contract with the Roar.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/brisbane-roar-sign-lucas-herrington-scholarship-contract-three-year-deal-latest-aleague-men-transfer-news/ |title=Roar hand 3-year scholarship contract to 'exciting talent' |date=9 September 2024 |website=A-Leagues}}</ref> He made his senior and professional debut as a starter in a 2–2 [[A-League Men]] draw against [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]] on 14 December 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/lucas-herrington-transfer-interest-brisbane-roar-ruben-zadkovich-youth-policy/ |title=Teen tipped for 'very, very big' transfer |date=19 February 2025 |website=A-Leagues}}</ref> On 28 January 2025, Herrington scored his first goal for Brisbane in a 4–3 win over [[Sydney FC]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dodd |first=James |date=2025-01-18 |title=Drought broken! Brisbane Roar STUN Sydney FC to earn first win of the season |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/aleague-men-sydney-fc-brisbane-roar-goals-highlights-match-report/ |access-date=2026-03-01 |website=A-Leagues |language=en-AU}}</ref> He made 17 appearances during his first professional season.

Herrington made his first appearance of the [[2025–26 Brisbane Roar FC season|2025–26 season]] as a substitute following a red card to [[Dimitri Valkanis]], helping see out a 1–0 win against [[Macarthur FC|Macarthur]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2025-10-17 |title=Roar fight tooth and nail to secure opening round win |url=https://brisbaneroar.com.au/news/roar-fight-tooth-and-nail-to-secure-opening-round-win/ |access-date=2026-03-01 |website=Brisbane Roar |language=en-AU}}</ref> He went on to make a further 10 appearances, scoring once in a 3–0 win over [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]] and keeping six clean sheets.

He played his final match for Brisbane Roar on 3 January 2026, starting in a 3–0 defeat to [[Wellington Phoenix FC|Wellington Phoenix]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Wellington stun Brisbane Roar at Redcliffe |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/wellington-stun-brisbane-roar-redcliffe/ |website=A-Leagues |date=3 January 2026 |access-date=3 January 2026}}</ref> Herrington made 29 appearances for the roar across all competitions, departing for a club record fee.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2025-08-13 |title=Brisbane Roar Academy product Lucas Herrington to transfer to Colorado Rapids for club record fee |url=https://brisbaneroar.com.au/news/brisbane-roar-academy-product-lucas-herrington-to-transfer-to-colorado-rapids-for-club-record-fee/ |access-date=2026-03-01 |website=Brisbane Roar |language=en-AU}}</ref>

=== Colorado Rapids ===
On 13 August 2025, Herrington agreed to join [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Colorado Rapids]] ahead of the 2026 season, with the transfer set to be completed in January 2026. He signed a contract running until 2029, with a club option for an additional year.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Colorado Rapids sign Australia youth international defender Lucas Herrington |url=https://www.coloradorapids.com/news/colorado-rapids-sign-australia-youth-international-defender-lucas-herrington |access-date=2026-03-01 |website=Colorado Rapids |language=en}}</ref>

On 22 February 2026, Herrington made his Major League Soccer debut for the Rapids in the opening round of the season, playing the full 90 minutes in a 2–0 loss to [[Seattle Sounders FC|Seattle Sounders]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rapids |first=Colorado |title=Recap {{!}} Rapids fall 2-0 on the road against Seattle Sounders |url=https://www.coloradorapids.com/news/recap-rapids-fall-to-seattle-in-2-0-loss-in-washington |access-date=2026-03-01 |website=Colorado Rapids |language=en}}</ref> A week later, on 28 February, he started in a 2–0 win over the [[Portland Timbers]], keeping his first clean sheet and scoring his first goal for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Recap {{!}} Ojediran, Herrington score as Rapids blank Portland 2-0 in Home Opener |url=https://www.coloradorapids.com/news/recap-ojediran-herrington-score-as-rapids-blank-portland-2-0-in-home-opener |access-date=2026-03-01 |website=Colorado Rapids |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Herrington was part of the [[Australia men's national under-19 soccer team|Australia U19]]s who came third at the [[2024 ASEAN U-19 Boys Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/subway-young-socceroos-squad-named-asean-u-19-boys-championship|title=Subway Young Socceroos squad named for ASEAN U-19 Boys’ Championship|publisher=[[Football Australia]]|website=[[Australia men's national soccer team|Socceroos]]|date=8 July 2024}}</ref> The following year, he was part of the [[Australia men's national under-20 soccer team|Australia U20]]s who won the [[2025 AFC U-20 Asian Cup]].<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/subway-young-socceroos-clinch-first-ever-afc-u20-asian-cup-title-historic-shootout-victory|title=Subway Young Socceroos clinch first-ever AFC U20 Asian Cup title in historic shootout victory &#124; Socceroos|date=1 March 2025|website=www.socceroos.com.au}}</ref>

He was called up in May 2025 for the [[Australia men's national under-20 soccer team#Current under-18 squad|Australia men's national under-18 soccer team]], to take part in the 2025 UEFA Friendship Cup commencing in early June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/australia-u18-squad-selected-uefa-friendship-cup-2025|title=Australia U18 Squad selected for UEFA Friendship Cup 2025|publisher=[[Football Australia]]|website=[[Australia men's national soccer team|Socceroos]]|date=20 May 2025}}</ref>

Herrington earned his maiden call-up to the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] national team for the [[FIFA Series]], where the Socceroos were scheduled to face [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] and [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-19 |title=CommBank Socceroos name three uncapped players for March FIFA Series 2026™ {{!}} Socceroos |url=https://socceroos.com.au/news/commbank-socceroos-name-three-uncapped-players-march-fifa-series-2026tm |access-date=2026-03-19 |website=socceroos.com.au |language=en}}</ref>

