==Personal life==
Herrington was born in [[Brisbane]], [[Queensland]] and attended the [[Anglican Church Grammar School]]. He is of [[Finnish Australians|Finnish]], [[German Australians|German]] and [[Zimbabwean Australians|Zimbabwean]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Danish delight: Aussie export making in-roads at AGF|url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/danish-delight-aussie-export-making-in-roads-at-agf-591991|publisher=ftbl.com.au|date=13 March 2023}}</ref> His older brother, [[Diesel Herrington]], is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://roundballaustralia.com.au/three-reasons-to-be-cheerful-about-brisbane-roar-in-2025/|title=Three reasons to be cheerful about Brisbane Roar in 2025|first=Kevan|last=Sangster|date=6 January 2025}}</ref>

